2.演出開始

Agnos Royal Guardsman: The King Agnos is going to battle!
Our king is with us! Oh king of the empire, the king who
fights!
Young Rex: Which way did my father go?

Queen Leucos: King Agnos has gone to battle for the peace of
the empire.

Young Rex: Mother said that battles are savage. Is there any
difference between my father's battles and savage battles?

Queen Leucos: The royal family refers to those who offer
prayers to the main god, Sol. We have the duty to protect
peace as representatives of Sol.

Queen Leucos: Fotizona is a word that means light... We must
deliver light to the world.

Queen Leucos: King Agnos' battles are battles that
illuminate the empire, battles that vanquish the minions of
darkness that shroud the empire.

Queen Leucos: Now, let us go to the Atomis Temple and pray
together for the victory of King Agnos, for the victory of
the empire.

Rex's mother, Leucos, was a devout follower of the Terios
religion. Deep down, she harbored bitter feelings towards
her husband, Agnos, who engaged in repeated battles. As a
result, she raised Rex with the expectation of him becoming
a tolerant and benevolent king.

King Agnos found his wife, who immersed herself in
fantasies, to be distasteful. He believed that being at the
forefront of the battlefield was the traditional image of a
king. Therefore, he educated Rex with the expectation of him
becoming a brave and valiant king.

Mother said that there is nothing more important than life.
Father said that there is something more important than
life. Rex's personality is formed within the contradiction
of these two values.

However, in general, my mother's teachings were dominant. I
had more opportunities to interact with my mother than with
my father, who often left the palace. It was because Rex
himself believed that peaceful resolutions were better.

However, Rex, like his father, also inherited the blood of a
king. The blood of a king that flows between two conflicting
values. The blood of a king slowly but surely seeped into
Rex's personality.

Within Rex, a monster was beginning to be born. Unbeknownst
to Rex, it was gradually growing larger, fueled by the blood
of a king.
